\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 My fellow citizens. At this hour, American and coalition forces are in the early stages of military operations to disarm \cf4 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 Iraq\cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 , to free its people and to defend the world from grave danger.\cb1 \
\cb3 "On my orders, coalition forces have begun striking selected targets of military importance to undermine Saddam Hussein's ability to wage war. These are opening stages of what will be a broad and concerted campaign.\cb1 \
\cb3 "More than 35 countries are giving crucial support from the use of naval and air bases to help with intelligence and logistics to deployment of combat units.\cb1 \
\cb3 "Every nation in this coalition has chosen to bear the duty and share the honour of serving in our common defence.\cb1 \
\cb3 "To all the men and women of the United States armed forces now in the Middle East, the peace of a troubled world and the hopes of an oppressed people now depend on you. That trust is well placed.\cb1 \
\cb3 "The enemies you confront will come to know your skill and bravery. The people you liberate will witness the honourable and decent spirit of the American military.\cb1 \
\cb3 "In this conflict America faces an enemy that has no regard for conventions of war or rules of morality.\cb1 \
\cb3 "Saddam Hussein has placed Iraqi troops and equipment in civilian areas, attempting to use innocent men, women and children as shields for his own military. A final atrocity against his people.\cb1 \
\cb3 "I want Americans and all the world to know that coalition forces will make every effort to spare innocent civilians from harm.\cb1 \
\cb3 "A campaign on the harsh terrain of the nation as large as California could be longer and more difficult than some predict and helping Iraqis achieve a united, stable and free country will require our sustained commitment.\cb1 \
\cb3 "We come to Iraq with respect for its citizens, for their great civilisation and for the religious faiths they practise.\cb1 \
