\cf2 \cb3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 "We have no ambition in Iraq except to remove a threat and restore control of that country to its own people.\cb1 \
\cb3 "I know that the families of our military are praying that all those who serve will return safely and soon.\cb1 \
\cb3 "Millions of Americans are praying with you for the safety of your loved ones and for the protection of the innocent.\cb1 \
\cb3 "For your sacrifice you have the gratitude and respect of the American people and you can know that our forces will be coming home as soon as their work is done.\cb1 \
\cb3 "Our nation enters this conflict reluctantly, yet our purpose is sure. The people of the United States and our friends and allies will not live at the mercy of an outlaw regime that threatens the peace with weapons of mass murder.\cb1 \
\cb3 "We will meet that threat now with our army, air force, navy, coastguard and marines so that we do not have to meet it later with armies of firefighters and police and doctors on the streets of our cities.\cb1 \
\cb3 "Now that conflict has come, the only way to limit its duration is to apply decisive force and I assure you this will not be a campaign of half measures and we will accept no outcome but victory.\cb1 \
\cb3 "My fellow citizens, the dangers to our country and the world will be overcome. We will pass through this time of peril and carry on the work of peace. We will defend our freedom. We will bring freedom to others and we will prevail.\cb1 \
\cb3 "May God bless our country and all who defend her."\cb1 \
